  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "```\r\n7.1. Subtleties. Note that while the initialisation code\r\nis executing, the newly created address exists but with no\r\nintrinsic body code.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis would imply that a contract which calls `CODESIZE` during its own initiation should expect the result to be 0 (which is not the case on any clients AFAIK).  We had a question related to this in the tests gitter room that led to some confusion on my part.  @pirapira I think it would be appropriate to add a footnote here to clarify the behavior of `CODESIZE` and `CODECOPY` during contract initiation.  \r\n\r\nWould you accept a PR for this?",
